        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer969828861" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7421417632210916706">You just would have to read Hafiz chanting:<br/>دل می‌رود ز دستم صاحب دلان خدا را<br/>دردا که راز پنهان خواهد شد آشکارا<br/><br/>and you don&apos;t have to look for translation because it is already singing by itself. If only we would think of Hafiz when we think of Irani women and men. What charming people and what beautiful heart. Hafiz is saying: <br/>O pious of the heart, I am lost in a love, so great<br/>O pain the hidden secrets will become open debate.<br/><br/> I also like what he has to say on wine:<br/>آن تلخ وش که صوفی ام الخبائثش خو</span>
  <span id="freeText7421417632210916706" style="display:none">You just would have to read Hafiz chanting:<br />دل می‌رود ز دستم صاحب دلان خدا را<br />دردا که راز پنهان خواهد شد آشکارا<br /><br />and you don't have to look for translation because it is already singing by itself. If only we would think of Hafiz when we think of Irani women and men. What charming people and what beautiful heart. Hafiz is saying: <br />O pious of the heart, I am lost in a love, so great<br />O pain the hidden secrets will become open debate.<br /><br /> I also like what he has to say on wine:<br />آن تلخ وش که صوفی ام الخبائثش خواند<br />اشهی لنا و احلی من قبله العذارا<br />that is, <br />You may call wine the mother of all uncleanness as long as you want; it is sweeter and tastier to me than the kiss of virgins.<br /><br />You just have to see how words rhyme in such a beautiful melody. I love Hafiz because he has such a sweet spirit, gentle heart, witty mind and amazing tact. When he passed away, people argued. Where can we bury him, he violated religion and as such we can't walk in his funeral. Well, they finally agreed after so much bickering to cast lots. When they drew one, it read:<br /><br />قدم دریغ مدار از جنازه حافظ . . که گر چه غرق گناه است می‌رود به بهشت <br /><br />which translates,<br /><br />Don't you dare miss out on the funeral of Havez. No dilly-dallying here! And by the way remember, while he is immersed in sins, he is yet going to Paradise for sure. <br />And what a lesson for us to shut our mouths, see the good in everybody and stop judging and let God be God. Let God alone decide who goes where!<br /> </span>
